roomModels.roomDescription: Gates can be seen just to the north on this cobblestone street, barely wide enough for two carriages to pass in either direction. Well kept yet simple stone homes sit on either side of the lane, providing a place to live for members of the peasantry. To the south, a large square can be seen in the distance, and to the east, the high inner walls of the Manor House. The cobblestones are well worn from the continuous traffic of carriages leaving town and returning from the countryside.
roomModels.roomTitle: CRAIGAVON LANE NORTH

roomModels.roomDescription: Outside the town square, you find yourself on a quiet, one carriage width lane. On the western side of the street sits the House of Lanfair, with large, marble columns on either side of its entrance, with several stately homes neighboring it. Next to the House of Lanfair is an alleyway, where there is just enough room for three carriages along with their horses.
roomModels.roomTitle: CRAIGAVON LANE SOUTH

roomModels.roomDescription: The bustling square gives way to a dead end side street, facing the giant cliffs and walls of the Manor House. On one side of the street, you see the Town Bank, and on the other, a stone storage house.
roomModels.roomTitle: TORRIDON LANE
THE NEXUS

roomModels.roomDescription: Before you is an immense town square, carefully paved with cobblestone and surrounded by ornate buildings. On the southern side of the square, space for merchants' tents is provided, and on the western side, a large open area suitable for large gatherings. To the east, the massive fortified walls of the Manor House are notable, standing above steep cliffs. Surrounding the square are a number of businesses, as well as homes of some of the wealthiest merchants in town.
roomModels.roomTitle: TOWN SQUARE

roomModels.roomDescription: On this narrow lane, homes line both sides of the street. A small locksmith can be seen on the western side of the lane.
roomModels.roomTitle: CRAIGAVON LANE SOUTH

roomModels.roomDescription: Flanking the town square on its northern side, this cobblestone lane is home to a small butcher shop and a blacksmith. The simple stone buildings are covered in a layer of soot from the constant burning of coal, needed to forge the tools and weaponry required by the townspeople. To the north, the town gates can be seen in the distance.
roomModels.roomTitle: CRAIGAVON LANE NORTH

roomModels.roomDescription: A stone archway marks the entrance to the city. Two guards armed with pikes stand at either side of the gate. Behind them are thick stone walls made of granite. The guards vigilantly observe the countryside past the city walls, ready to defend the town against the dangers which lie outside. Above, you notice two guard towers on either side of the gate, with archers positioned in each.
roomModels.roomTitle: NORTH GATE
